# Claudstermind .gitignore
#
# Claudstermind holds text knowledge about projects — conventions, state,
# learnings. Secrets (tokens, SSH keys, API keys, passwords) MUST NEVER
# land here in the first place. This .gitignore is belt-and-suspenders:
# if something secret-shaped accidentally gets written, we catch it
# before `git add -A` stages it.
#
# The skills/push.md protocol also aborts pushes when files matching
# these patterns are detected in the staging area.

# Editors / OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Environment / secrets (must never be here; guarded anyway)
.env
.env.*
*.env
*.key
*.pem
*.pfx
*.p12
*.token
*.credentials
secrets/
private/

# Local token storage (::cmpush reads from here — MUST stay out of git)
.secret/

# Scratch / WIP (owner-local notes the owner doesn't want in the cluster history)
scratch/
_WIP/
*.draft.md

# Node / build artifacts (in case a project folder gets nested by accident)
node_modules/
dist/
build/
*.log

# Token hygiene inventory — metadata only, but recon-sensitive (which tokens exist where). Never commit.
dashboard/data/tokens.json
.media/

# Relay bridge config (points at the online relay; recon-sensitive). Never commit.
dashboard/data/relay.json
cm-deploy.tgz
